Oak Street, east from and including James Street.
September 9, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

original_title: Manhattan: New Chambers Street - James Street
text:
(1) At the intersection of New Chambers and James Streets. Also shown is New Chambers Street, north side, west from Cherry Street, to and including New Bowery. Included also is James Street, west side, north from and including New Chambers Street, to and including New Bowery. The Second and Third Ave., Elevated is shown in the background at New Bowery.

May 3, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, from a different angle, and showing James Street, east side, north from but not including Cherry Street, to and including New Bowery. Public School No. 114, is shown on James Street, at the S.E. corner of Oak Street.

May 3, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, as No. 1, at a later date, showing in the background, and from right to left, the Municipal Building and the New Federal Courts Building, the second of these under construction.

July 27, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

1932.
